        "baseRefName": "master",
        "body": "Over a field of characteristic zero.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nI expect that the headline result could be made to work over any principal ideal domain (of characteristic zero) instead of a field. The plan I see would be to define the nilradical of a Lie algebra (currently missing) and use it with `LieModule.exists_nontrivial_weightSpace_of_isNilpotent` instead of using the solvable radical with Lie's theorem in `LieAlgebra.hasCentralRadical_and_of_isIrreducible_of_isFaithful`. The conclusion should become that the nilradical vanishes. We would prove elsewhere that vanishing nilradical is equivalent to `HasCentralRadical`.\r\n\r\n\r\n[![Open in Gitpod](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/from-referrer/)\r\n",
